        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 2:27PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 227 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Franklin to near Greensburg. These storms
were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Franklin, Greensburg, Adams, Edinburgh, Flat Rock, Milford, Princes
Lakes, Geneva, St. Paul, Marietta, Waldron, and Sandusky.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 65 between mile markers 79 and 90.
Interstate 74 between mile markers 121 and 138.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
